description: Ustawi, founded in 2019, is based in Laikipia County, Kenya, with its headquarters in Newquay Town. The initiative focuses on empowering rural women through agriculture, enhancing food production, and ensuring food security. Ustawi offers services such as access to agricultural resources, training in sustainable practices, and financial support, aiming to transform communities and promote economic empowerment while addressing challenges like climate change and cultural biases.
name: Ustawi
